Meetings & Corporate Events
From business meetings and lectures to fundraisers, networking events, and private dinners or cocktail receptions, Oxford Exchange is your one-stop destination for hosting exceptional events. Experience our historic venue, where we provide authentic hospitality and all food and beverage services in-house.
________
Meeting Rooms & Private Event Spaces
Daytime Event Spaces -
available from 8:00 AM to 5:30 PM
The Commerce Club
Located on the second floor, The Commerce Club offers a variety of flexible spaces, including three meeting rooms, a podcast and recording room, and a spacious coworking area that can also function as an event space.
Keynes Room
Podcast & Recording Room  Up to 6 people
Friedman Room.
Up to 8 people
Hayek Room
Up to 12 people
Smith Room
Up to 24 people
Shaw Library
30–80 seated, 180 lecture-style
The Commerce Club is also available for corporate buyouts, making it an ideal setting for business retreats and multi-day conferences.
After-Hours Event Spaces  -
available starting at 6:30 PM
Oxford Exchange transforms after business hours to accommodate private dinners or cocktail receptions for up to 250 guests.
Atrium
100 guests (cocktail-style)
Atrium & Conservatory
80 seated / 125 cocktail-style
Atrium, Conservatory & Champagne Bar
150 cocktail-style
Entire First Level
200 seated / 250 cocktail-style

The Commerce Club at Oxford Exchange is a private, comfortable, and flexible business resource, as well as coworking space for individuals who work from home in the Tampa Bay area.
